OL,3,CMum spent final year in 'pain and
OL,4,Csqualor' after son pulled her out of
OL,5,Ccare home
OL,7,FA 94-year-old woman was left to live
OL,8,Fin "pain and squalor" during the final
OL,9,Fmonths of her life after her son
OL,10,Ffailed to care for her.
OL,12,FLilian Walsh was covered in bruises
OL,13,Fand suffering from severe pressure
OL,14,Fsores when paramedics discovered her
OL,15,Fin her son's home in Ramsbottom. Two
OL,16,Fdays later, she died in hospital.
OL,18,FLilian was living with dementia in a
OL,19,Fnearby care home up until January 2018
OL,20,Fwhen her son, a 72-year-old Graham
OL,21,FWalsh, discharged her into his care.
